69
00:08:08,032 --> 00:08:09,413
[SPEAKER_18]: Thank you, Dr. Galluzzi.

70
00:08:09,793 --> 00:08:11,314
[SPEAKER_18]: Hello, members of the school committee.

71
00:08:11,374 --> 00:08:12,115
[SPEAKER_18]: May it long occur.

72
00:08:12,875 --> 00:08:27,525
[SPEAKER_18]: So tonight, we're going to take a Mustang moment to allow voices from the McGlynn Elementary School to share their experiences with an online math program called ST Math.

73
00:08:28,025 --> 00:08:30,627
[SPEAKER_18]: We are in year one of a three-year grant.

74
00:08:31,547 --> 00:08:40,202
[SPEAKER_18]: And the unique aspect of ST Math is that it challenges kids to exercise a problem-solving process without any written instructions.

75
00:08:41,488 --> 00:08:51,214
[SPEAKER_18]: They see the problem, they think about the problem, they try the problem, and then they learn from the problem, and then they demonstrate how they know it.

76
00:08:51,714 --> 00:08:56,357
[SPEAKER_18]: So in essence, ST Math encourages students to make mistakes so that they can learn.

77
00:08:57,237 --> 00:08:58,158
[SPEAKER_18]: So we're very excited.

78
00:08:58,318 --> 00:08:59,879
[SPEAKER_18]: It's been a big hit this year.

