[SPEAKER_09]: So I just wanted to start by thanking everyone for the opportunity to share tonight's district update with everyone.

204
00:20:45,303 --> 00:21:00,354
[SPEAKER_09]: As we move further into the academic year, our central office team remains focused on aligning our work and our resources to our core mission of providing students with high quality instructional learning environments

205
00:21:02,075 --> 00:21:07,018
[SPEAKER_09]: So this evening, as the mayor has stated, I'm gonna start with a brief update on the calendar.

206
00:21:07,618 --> 00:21:17,723
[SPEAKER_09]: Dr. Talbot will update us on academics and instruction work, and Mr. Ken Lord will update us on some operational work that's happening throughout the district.

207
00:21:20,743 --> 00:21:30,589
[SPEAKER_09]: But before we get to all that, I also want to pause and take a moment to reflect on some news.

208
00:21:31,050 --> 00:21:43,718
[SPEAKER_09]: So our Director of Student Services, Joan Bowen, after 33 years of dedicated service to Medford Public Schools, she will be retiring in September 2026.

209
00:21:45,699 --> 00:22:01,508
[SPEAKER_09]: I think it's important to just take a moment and pause because three decades is something that is incredibly significant and I cannot imagine the number of families that she and her service has directly impacted in Medford Public Schools.

210
00:22:01,568 --> 00:22:10,573
[SPEAKER_09]: I think she's at the point where she is seeing children of children that she has worked with and alongside in the district.

211
00:22:10,673 --> 00:22:11,393
[SPEAKER_09]: So in her 33 years,

212
00:22:13,414 --> 00:22:19,298
[SPEAKER_09]: Joan was a special education teacher at the Hillside Alternative School and Andrews Middle School.

213
00:22:20,379 --> 00:22:23,361
[SPEAKER_09]: One of those schools no longer exists in the city of Medford.

214
00:22:23,941 --> 00:22:35,469
[SPEAKER_09]: She also served the city as an evaluation team leader, as a coordinator for special education and most recently the director of student services.

215
00:22:36,330 --> 00:22:38,271
[SPEAKER_09]: So her impact is profound.

216
00:22:39,291 --> 00:22:41,292
[SPEAKER_09]: We have some big shoes to fill.

217
00:22:42,933 --> 00:23:00,919
[SPEAKER_09]: In the coming days, we are going to be sending out a survey for our staff, our students, our caregivers, our community, just around some special education areas or input.

218
00:23:00,979 --> 00:23:03,320
[SPEAKER_09]: We want to gather some input before we move to

219
00:23:06,619 --> 00:23:13,104
[SPEAKER_09]: put together a selection committee to talk about the hiring process for this position.

220
00:23:13,184 --> 00:23:19,448
[SPEAKER_09]: So first we're going to gather some input and then we're going to reach out again for next steps of putting together a search committee.

221
00:23:20,409 --> 00:23:23,451
[SPEAKER_09]: You will see that come out in a separate, I think, tomorrow.

222
00:23:23,772 --> 00:23:25,373
[SPEAKER_09]: We have it queued with Mr. Pippicelli.

223
00:23:26,574 --> 00:23:28,675
[SPEAKER_09]: Staff to this point has been informed.

224
00:23:28,695 --> 00:23:31,918
[SPEAKER_09]: Joan has taken a very thoughtful approach to informing everyone.

225
00:23:32,718 --> 00:23:35,080
[SPEAKER_09]: And we're going to kind of put it out broadly

226
00:23:36,320 --> 00:23:46,103
[SPEAKER_09]: So just wanted to make sure that we acknowledge Joan and we will have further updates in the coming weeks as she is here until September 2026.

227
00:23:46,743 --> 00:23:51,185
[SPEAKER_09]: So it does allow for a really nice transition period for Metro Public Schools.

228
00:23:51,525 --> 00:23:54,426
[SPEAKER_09]: So thank you, Joan, for everything you've done.

229
00:23:54,506 --> 00:23:59,107
[SPEAKER_09]: And I wanted to make sure we commented on that this evening.

230
00:24:01,128 --> 00:24:01,348
[SPEAKER_09]: Yeah.

231
00:24:09,339 --> 00:24:12,862
[SPEAKER_09]: OK, moving on to school calendar.

232
00:24:14,763 --> 00:24:24,510
[SPEAKER_09]: Due to the four snow days that we've had, two at the end of January, two following the February vacation, it has impacted our school calendar.

233
00:24:25,051 --> 00:24:28,853
[SPEAKER_09]: So first and foremost, I think it's important we have updated this on the website.

234
00:24:28,913 --> 00:24:32,116
[SPEAKER_09]: So if anybody goes to the website, the calendar is already updated.

235
00:24:32,616 --> 00:24:36,219
[SPEAKER_09]: But it does bring our last day of school to Wednesday, June 24.

