579
00:55:09,178 --> 00:55:17,462
[SPEAKER_00]: There will be pictures available of all of the 29 options so people can continue to weigh in as they think about space and

580
00:55:18,009 --> 00:55:20,491
[SPEAKER_00]: In space planning on the kinds of things that they like.

581
00:55:21,111 --> 00:55:30,918
[SPEAKER_00]: So all this in an effort to collect lots of good feedback from from the community, but it is in person only because of the Lego block.

582
00:55:32,301 --> 00:55:35,383
[SPEAKER_00]: So we've got that going on this week.

583
00:55:37,505 --> 00:55:47,954
[SPEAKER_00]: Earlier today a robocall went out from the city informing everyone on the robocall list about how to get involved in the project, where to go for information.

584
00:55:47,994 --> 00:55:48,835
[SPEAKER_00]: That is happening.

585
00:55:49,555 --> 00:55:53,399
[SPEAKER_00]: We're also investigating whether we send a citywide mailer.

586
00:55:54,679 --> 00:56:02,362
[SPEAKER_00]: to, again, alert people at this early stage to understand, A, that this project is happening in case there are people who don't know.

587
00:56:02,382 --> 00:56:03,962
[SPEAKER_00]: I think lots and lots of people know.

588
00:56:05,182 --> 00:56:12,745
[SPEAKER_00]: But those who don't will have an opportunity then to sort of tune in, sign up for an email list, go to the website, follow along, et cetera.

589
00:56:14,386 --> 00:56:19,612
[SPEAKER_00]: And then as we move forward, there's a couple of big things that'll be happening in the next two months.

590
00:56:20,873 --> 00:56:32,486
[SPEAKER_00]: One is at the end of this month, on the 23rd of March, we'll be sort of digging in deeper at our building committee meeting on the evaluation criteria that we spent some time talking about last week.

591
00:56:34,748 --> 00:56:58,697
[SPEAKER_00]: and really thinking through as a committee like how does this evaluation criteria sort of lay out across what is currently like 29 options and start to do some thinking about anything that we may want to change about that initial ranking or adjust about the space summary or any of those kinds of things could be on the agenda on the 23rd.

592
00:57:01,938 --> 00:57:10,244
[SPEAKER_00]: 27th of April right after April vacation is the meeting where we will actually go from 29 options to three to five.

593
00:57:11,205 --> 00:57:12,906
[SPEAKER_00]: So that will be a big important meeting.

594
00:57:14,026 --> 00:57:18,890
[SPEAKER_00]: We also have a meeting coming up with our project of butters in March.

595
00:57:19,450 --> 00:57:30,342
[SPEAKER_00]: So we're inviting them in to talk, to just have some dedicated time with architects and our OPM just to understand sort of what's on the mind of our abutters.

596
00:57:30,602 --> 00:57:37,470
[SPEAKER_00]: Actually, this project doesn't have tons of abutters because DCR is one of our biggest neighbors.

597
00:57:39,511 --> 00:57:44,053
[SPEAKER_00]: But we are doing some continued effort to reach out to those abutters.

598
00:57:44,453 --> 00:57:49,176
[SPEAKER_00]: They'll get a postcard maybe this week or next week with the dates of some abutter-specific meetings.

599
00:57:49,736 --> 00:57:52,798
[SPEAKER_00]: They got hand-delivered letters back in November.

600
00:57:53,678 --> 00:57:57,460
[SPEAKER_00]: And we just want to hear from them on an ongoing basis so that we're

601
00:57:58,241 --> 00:58:00,003
[SPEAKER_00]: being responsible neighbors as well.

602
00:58:01,024 --> 00:58:18,998
[SPEAKER_00]: And then the other big thing that happened in the last week was that we did make a decision as a committee to pursue this project as a CM at risk project, which means that we'll bring the construction manager on during schematic design rather than pursuing design bid build, which is

603
00:58:19,799 --> 00:58:22,221
[SPEAKER_00]: tends to be easier on less complex projects.

604
00:58:22,301 --> 00:58:44,862
[SPEAKER_00]: Maybe projects are a little bit smaller, but this project really lends itself to getting all the people on the team as quickly as possible to make the best decisions and make sure that the building that gets designed can be built, which is always sort of a weird limbo space if you ever build anything between the intent on paper and what can actually happen in person.

605
00:58:46,981 --> 00:58:48,501
[SPEAKER_00]: So all of that is coming.

606
00:58:50,482 --> 00:58:59,246
[SPEAKER_00]: There's lots more to come and we are moving towards by the end of June we will down select to a single option to pursue.

607
00:58:59,266 --> 00:59:08,850
[SPEAKER_00]: But between now and then there's some interim steps that we'll take and some like lots of refinement of different parts of the project.

608
00:59:09,390 --> 00:59:11,511
[SPEAKER_00]: We'll hone in on a handful of options.

609
00:59:11,551 --> 00:59:14,853
[SPEAKER_00]: We'll do a more in-depth cost estimate on those options.

610
00:59:16,003 --> 00:59:27,526
[SPEAKER_00]: after April 27th, all to help continue to inform the building committee of what's happening, what the choices are, and then how to go about making those decisions the best way we can for Medford.

611
00:59:29,406 --> 00:59:35,028
[SPEAKER_00]: I think that's everything in terms of what we've been up to on the MSBA project.

612
00:59:35,828 --> 00:59:36,288
[SPEAKER_00]: Any questions?

613
00:59:36,308 --> 00:59:36,968
