621
01:00:09,924 --> 01:00:22,808
[SPEAKER_00]: There's lots of other reasons for the building committee to have some time to think through some of the options because there was a whole lot of choices really sort of presented as part of the cost scenarios.

622
01:00:23,309 --> 01:00:27,490
[SPEAKER_00]: The goal with those choices was to say that we left no stone unturned, right?

623
01:00:28,450 --> 01:00:34,875
[SPEAKER_00]: When somebody comes back and says, hey, did you ever think about if the pool was twice as big as it was or if it was half as big as it was?

624
01:00:35,775 --> 01:00:40,238
[SPEAKER_00]: We have lots and lots of cost data to be able to help facilitate those what ifs.

625
01:00:41,319 --> 01:00:46,183
[SPEAKER_00]: And so there's some natural working through of options that has to happen in the coming

626
01:00:47,003 --> 01:00:56,596
[SPEAKER_00]: And then the, I'll say the third and final thing is because we do want to be thoughtful about how we evaluate.

627
01:00:56,737 --> 01:00:59,560
