648
01:03:01,298 --> 01:03:02,219
[SPEAKER_00]: Oh, jeez, I'm sorry.

649
01:03:02,519 --> 01:03:02,940
[SPEAKER_00]: New business.

650
01:03:03,652 --> 01:03:15,483
[SPEAKER_10]: Offered by Member Graham, be it resolved that the Medford School Committee review and approve a revised capital plan inclusive of priority ratings, as requested by the Collins Center, who's working to refresh the City of Medford's broader capital plan.

651
01:03:15,823 --> 01:03:16,224
[SPEAKER_10]: Member Graham.

652
01:03:16,845 --> 01:03:17,666
[SPEAKER_00]: Yes, thank you.

653
01:03:18,686 --> 01:03:29,494
[SPEAKER_00]: After we approved our capital plan late last year, we turned it over to the Collins Center, who is working with the city to refresh the city's broader capital plan.

654
01:03:30,114 --> 01:03:43,004
[SPEAKER_00]: And they came back to Ken and I and asked that we add a prioritization that lined up with how they are prioritizing projects across the city, which was just a little bit different than the approach that we took.

655
01:03:44,105 --> 01:03:46,467
[SPEAKER_00]: You can see that in the column on the left.

656
01:03:46,967 --> 01:03:52,472
[SPEAKER_00]: They asked us just to rank the projects in order from one until whatever.

657
01:03:52,492 --> 01:03:53,633
[SPEAKER_00]: I think in this case it's like 35.

658
01:03:55,690 --> 01:04:04,014
[SPEAKER_00]: 30, we had taken an approach of, like, here's what we want to do each year, and there was some prioritization and grouping within ours.

659
01:04:04,094 --> 01:04:12,397
[SPEAKER_00]: So, this was our, this was my attempt in collaboration with Ken to say, how do we translate what this group approved to

660
01:04:15,199 --> 01:04:21,983
[SPEAKER_00]: something that like meshes a little bit better with how the city's capital plan is being refreshed and revised.

661
01:04:22,824 --> 01:04:34,071
[SPEAKER_00]: So I did, we have provided this to the Collins Center already to sort of enable them to do this work, but I did let them know that this body would need to like re-approve this capital plan, particularly with these prioritizations.

662
01:04:34,151 --> 01:04:36,853
[SPEAKER_00]: So I'm hoping that we can do that tonight.

663
01:04:44,922 --> 01:04:45,542
[SPEAKER_10]: Is there a second?

664
01:04:47,344 --> 01:04:47,644
[SPEAKER_10]: Second?

665
01:04:49,505 --> 01:04:51,626
[SPEAKER_10]: My member Graham, all those in favor?

666
01:04:52,307 --> 01:04:52,427
[SPEAKER_10]: Aye.

667
01:04:52,647 --> 01:04:53,408
[SPEAKER_10]: All those opposed?

668
01:04:53,928 --> 01:04:54,708
[SPEAKER_10]: Motion carries.

669
01:04:57,090 --> 01:04:58,311
[SPEAKER_10]: And now on to our condolence.

670
01:04:58,351 --> 01:05:09,838
[SPEAKER_10]: The members of the Medford School Committee express their sincerest condolences to the family of Marta J. McNulty McGowan, who worked for the Medford Public Schools for over 40 years.

671
01:05:09,858 --> 01:05:12,000
[SPEAKER_10]: If we all may rise for a moment of silence, please.

672
01:05:22,243 --> 01:05:22,583
[SPEAKER_10]: Thank you.

673
01:05:24,424 --> 01:05:31,929
[SPEAKER_10]: Our next regular meeting of the Medford School Committee will be March 16th, 2026 here in the Alden Memorial Chambers and via Zoom.

674
01:05:35,892 --> 01:05:39,754
[SPEAKER_10]: Motion to adjourn by Member Graham, seconded by Member Mastroboni.

675
01:05:39,814 --> 01:05:40,595
